From: Florent Revest <revestflo@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 5 Jun 2026 21:30:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] audio: monaco: bind haptics codec by deterministic MFD child
 name
Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [aurora-specific HW glue]

monaco's haptics dai_links reference the cs40l26 codec component by
the literal name "cs40l26-codec.2.auto". That is the auto-numbered
platform-device name the i2c-driven MFD child gets on stock WearOS,
where the global PLATFORM_DEVID_AUTO allocation order happens to give
it id 2. With our module set/load order the id differs, so
snd_soc_register_card() deferred forever waiting for a component
that never appears by that name.

An earlier version of this patch "fixed" the deferral by switching
the dai_links to "cs40l26_codec", the aurora DT's asoc-codec-names
entry, so monaco's of_property_match_string() remap resolved the
codec by of_node. That bound the WRONG component: the asoc-codec
phandle points at a compatible-less "cs40l26-codec" child node of
bolero-cdc, and bolero_add_child_devices() spawns a platform device
named after that node (parented to the bolero device) which
string-matches the cs40l26-codec platform driver. That driver's
probe does

    cs40l26 = dev_get_drvdata(pdev->dev.parent);

which on the bolero-spawned instance yields bolero's private struct,
not the real cs40l26_private (the cs40l26_loaded global gate passes
because the genuine i2c probe already ran). The resulting component
is the only one whose of_node matches the card, so the card binds it
with codec->core pointing into bolero_priv. Reading any kcontrol
that chases core->dsp ('A2H Level', numid 150 -- the first control
AGM's enumeration sweep hits when the card comes ONLINE) then walks
a "list head" that actually contains module .text, the bogus
dereference hard-hangs the bus, and the SoC dies in a silent PS_HOLD
HARD_RESET. Stock WearOS carries the same poisoned instance but its
machine driver never binds it; the asoc-codec-names entry is
vestigial there.

Bind the healthy MFD child instead, like stock does, but by a
deterministic name: the companion amplifiers patch pins the MFD
child platform id to 0, so the component is always
"cs40l26-codec.0" regardless of probe order.

Signed-off-by: Florent Revest <revestflo@gmail.com>
---
 private/msm-google-modules/audio/asoc/msm_monaco_dailink.h | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/private/msm-google-modules/audio/asoc/msm_monaco_dailink.h b/private/msm-google-modules/audio/asoc/msm_monaco_dailink.h
--- a/private/msm-google-modules/audio/asoc/msm_monaco_dailink.h
+++ b/private/msm-google-modules/audio/asoc/msm_monaco_dailink.h
@@ -158,11 +158,11 @@ SND_SOC_DAILINK_DEFS(pri_mi2s_tx,

 SND_SOC_DAILINK_DEFS(sec_mi2s_haptics_rx,
 	DAILINK_COMP_ARRAY(COMP_CPU("snd-soc-dummy-dai")),
-	DAILINK_COMP_ARRAY(COMP_CODEC("cs40l26-codec.2.auto", "cs40l26-pcm")),
+	DAILINK_COMP_ARRAY(COMP_CODEC("cs40l26-codec.0", "cs40l26-pcm")),
 	DAILINK_COMP_ARRAY(COMP_PLATFORM("snd-soc-dummy")));

 SND_SOC_DAILINK_DEFS(pri_mi2s_haptics_rx,
 	DAILINK_COMP_ARRAY(COMP_CPU("snd-soc-dummy-dai")),
-	DAILINK_COMP_ARRAY(COMP_CODEC("cs40l26-codec.2.auto", "cs40l26-pcm")),
+	DAILINK_COMP_ARRAY(COMP_CODEC("cs40l26-codec.0", "cs40l26-pcm")),
 	DAILINK_COMP_ARRAY(COMP_PLATFORM("snd-soc-dummy")));
 #endif
